# Docker Setup and Configuration

## Container Configuration
The main application container is defined in [Dockerfile](mdc:Dockerfile) and includes:
- PHP 8.2 with FPM
- Required PHP extensions
- System dependencies
- Composer and NPM
- User setup for development

## DevContainer Configuration
The Codespaces/DevContainer setup is defined in [devcontainer.json](mdc:.codespaces/devcontainer.json) and provides:
- Container configuration
- VS Code extensions
- Service definitions (MySQL, Redis)
- Port forwarding
- User settings

## Service Dependencies
The system requires the following services:
- MySQL 8.0
- Redis (Alpine)
- PHP-FPM
- Nginx (optional)

## Environment Variables
Required environment variables for services:
- MySQL:
  - MYSQL_ROOT_PASSWORD
  - MYSQL_DATABASE
  - MYSQL_USER
  - MYSQL_PASSWORD
- Redis:
  - Default configuration (no auth required)

## Port Mappings
- 8000: Application server
- 3306: MySQL
- 6379: Redis
